{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 3. Installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Step 1 \u8212- Install the package\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If you have the {\f1 .deb} file (e.g.\u160 ?in {\f1 ~/Downloads}):\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 sudo dpkg -i ~/Downloads/win11-window-tiling_1.0.0_all.deb\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Step 2 \u8212- Fix missing dependencies (if prompted)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 sudo apt install -f\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This installs recommended packages such as {\f1 wmctrl}, {\f1 xdotool}, and {\f1 xbindkeys}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Step 3 \u8212- Verify installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 dpkg -l win11-window-tiling\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You should see {\f1 Status: install ok installed}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Step 4 \u8212- Run setup\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 win11-tiling-setup\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Step 5 \u8212- Log out and back in\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Tiling extensions and autostart entries need a fresh session to take effect.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
