gnome)\line
GNOME extension:  installed\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 What setup does (by desktop)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b GNOME} - Installs the Tiling Shell extension to {\f1 ~/.local/share/gnome-shell/extensions/} - Enables the extension via {\f1 gnome-extensions} (if available) - Uses the modern or legacy extension build based on your GNOME Shell version\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b KDE Plasma} - Copies the KZones KWin script to {\f1 ~/.local/share/kwin/scripts/} - Loads and runs the script via KWin\u8217's scripting API - Configures Windows 11-style {\f1 Super} + arrow shortcuts in KGlobalAccel\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b X11 fallback} - Copies hotkey config to {\f1 ~/.config/win11-tiling/xbindkeysrc} - Adds an autostart entry so {\f1 xbindkeys} starts on login - Starts {\f1 xbindkeys} immediately if it is installed\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
