{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 Custom layouts (Fancy Zones)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In Tiling Shell settings:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Open the {\b Layouts} section.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Create or import custom tile grids.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Assign layouts per monitor and per workspace.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Use {\b Cycle layouts} keybindings (assign in the Keybindings section).\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 Change keyboard shortcuts (GNOME)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In Tiling Shell settings \u8594 ? {\b Keybindings}:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Move window left/right/up/down\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Span window across tiles\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Untile window\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Focus next/previous tiled window\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Cycle layouts\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Defaults match Windows 11 ({\f1 Super} + arrows). Change any binding to your preference.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 GNOME settings via command line\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 # Example: disable snap assist\line
gsettings set org.gnome.shell.extensions.tilingshell enable-snap-assist false\line
\line
# Example: increase gap between tiles\line
gsettings set org.gnome.shell.extensions.tilingshell inner-gaps 24\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 KDE \u8212- KZones and shortcuts\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Zone layouts:} System Settings \u8594 ? Window Management \u8594 ? KWin Scripts \u8594 ? KZones\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Keyboard shortcuts:} System Settings \u8594 ? Shortcuts \u8594 ? KWin\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The setup script pre-configures {\f1 Meta} (Super) + arrow shortcuts. Adjust them in KWin shortcut settings if they conflict with other bindings.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 X11 \u8212- xbindkeys config\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 User config file:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 ~/.config/win11-tiling/xbindkeysrc\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Edit this file to change hotkeys. Example entry:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 "win11-tile left"\line
  Mod4 + Left\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\f1 Mod4} is the Super/Windows key.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 After editing, restart xbindkeys:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 pkill xbindkeys\line
xbindkeys -f ~/.config/win11-tiling/xbindkeysrc\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Or log out and back in (autostart handles it).\par}
