{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 GNOME: extension not working after setup\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Check it is enabled:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi0 \f1 gnome-extensions list --enabled | grep tilingshell\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab If missing, enable it:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi0 \f1 gnome-extensions enable tilingshell@ferrarodomenico.com\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Re-run setup:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi0 \f1 win11-tiling-setup --gnome\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab {\b Log out and back in} (required after installing a GNOME Shell extension).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab If the extension shows as \u8220"incompatible\u8221", your GNOME Shell version may not be supported. Check:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi0 \f1 gnome-shell --version\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi0 Tiling Shell in this package supports GNOME Shell 45\u8211-49.\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 GNOME: Super + arrow does nothing\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Another extension or GNOME setting may be using the same shortcuts.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Open {\b Tiling Shell \u8594 ? Keybindings} and verify bindings are set.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Confirm {\b Enable keybindings} is turned on.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Check for conflicts in {\b Settings \u8594 ? Keyboard \u8594 ? Keyboard Shortcuts}.\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 KDE: zones or shortcuts not working\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Verify the script is installed:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi0 \f1 ls ~/.local/share/kwin/scripts/kzones.kwinscript\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Re-run setup:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi0 \f1 win11-tiling-setup --kde\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Restart KWin or log out and back in.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Check {\b System Settings \u8594 ? Shortcuts} for conflicting {\f1 Meta} bindings.\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 X11: hotkeys not working\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Confirm dependencies:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi0 \f1 sudo apt install wmctrl xdotool xbindkeys\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Check xbindkeys is running:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi0 \f1 pgrep -a xbindkeys\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Start manually:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi0 \f1 xbindkeys -f ~/.config/win11-tiling/xbindkeysrc\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Test tiling directly:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi0 \f1 win11-tile left\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Wayland warning during setup\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If you see:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 WARNING: Wayland session without native GNOME/KDE support.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You are on a Wayland session that is not GNOME or KDE. The X11 fallback has limited Wayland support. Use GNOME or KDE for full tiling, or switch to an X11 session.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Package won\u8217't install\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If {\f1 dpkg} reports a control file error, ensure you have the rebuilt package (fixed trailing newline in the control file). Re-download or rebuild, then:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 sudo dpkg -i ~/Downloads/win11-window-tiling_1.0.0_all.deb\line
sudo apt install -f\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 10. Uninstalling\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Remove user configuration only\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 win11-tiling-setup --uninstall\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This removes: - {\f1 ~/.config/win11-tiling/} - GNOME Tiling Shell extension (user copy) - KDE KZones script - X11 autostart entry - Running {\f1 xbindkeys} process\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Log out and back in after uninstalling user config.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Remove the package entirely\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 win11-tiling-setup --uninstall\line
sudo apt remove win11-window-tiling\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
